The paper deals with finding an optimal assignment between two sets of objects, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The application areas mentioned, such as natural language processing and computer vision, suggest that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of tree distances and the development of an algorithm for linear time computation suggest that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of optimization techniques and the development of an efficient algorithm suggest that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
